--- Quick Reference Guide ---

 {"type":"h3","text":"**Quick Reference Guide**"}
 {"type":"breakdown","labels":{"title":"Question Type","text":"Goal & The #1 Trap"},"items":[...]}

{ "type": "diff-note", "text": "The Quick Reference covers 9 types but the main guide defines 14. The 5 missing types are: Structure/Organization, Phrase Meaning, 3rd-Party Viewpoint, Application/Hypothetical, and Passage Principle.", "variant": "comment" }

+{{+Add the following 5 missing entries to the Quick Reference:+}}
+{{+**Structure/Organization** -- Goal: Map the passage's logical flow. Trap: One step in the sequence is wrong.+}}
+{{+**Phrase Meaning** -- Goal: Define by context, not dictionary. Trap: Standard definition when author means something different.+}}
+{{+**3rd-Party Viewpoint** -- Goal: Report what THEY believe. Trap: Attributing the author's view to the 3rd party.+}}
+{{+**Application/Hypothetical** -- Goal: Apply the passage's rule to a new case. Trap: Misses one condition of the rule.+}}
+{{+**Passage Principle** -- Goal: Find the general rule behind the specific judgment. Trap: Restates the specific case, not the abstract rule.+}}

